So we can try to
isolate this big piece,

01:03:00.000 --> 01:03:03.970 align:middle line:84%
so we will make a
slight transformation.

01:03:03.970 --> 01:03:12.700 align:middle line:84%
So we write phi equal to
exponential minus i m t capital

01:03:12.700 --> 01:03:13.730 align:middle line:90%
phi.

01:03:13.730 --> 01:03:23.480 align:middle line:84%
And the chi equal to i
m t x or capital chi.

01:03:23.480 --> 01:03:29.150 align:middle line:84%
So now this will only
contain this low energy part,

01:03:29.150 --> 01:03:31.250 align:middle line:84%
so those field will only
contain the low energy

01:03:31.250 --> 01:03:35.600 align:middle line:84%
part that already isolated
the big things in here.

01:03:35.600 --> 01:03:38.330 align:middle line:84%
So the time dependence here will
only include the low energy.

01:03:38.330 --> 01:03:41.130 align:middle line:90%


01:03:41.130 --> 01:03:46.570 align:middle line:84%
So we assume that as a t
phi would be mv squared,

01:03:46.570 --> 01:04:04.560 align:middle line:84%
so phi similarly this X.
Similarly this X. So this is

01:04:04.560 --> 01:04:07.110 align:middle line:84%
the fast oscillator
part in time,

01:04:07.110 --> 01:04:09.720 align:middle line:90%
this is the slow part in time.

01:04:09.720 --> 01:04:15.770 align:middle line:84%
So now we plug this in
to these two equations.

01:04:15.770 --> 01:04:19.860 align:middle line:90%
Plugged into those equations.

01:04:19.860 --> 01:04:24.750 align:middle line:90%
Then we find i partial t.

01:04:24.750 --> 01:04:29.080 align:middle line:90%


01:04:29.080 --> 01:04:34.510 align:middle line:84%
i partial t phi
equal to sigma dot

01:04:34.510 --> 01:04:49.390 align:middle line:84%
pi x plus eA0 phi and i
partial tx equal to 2 minus mx.

01:04:49.390 --> 01:04:53.040 align:middle line:90%


01:04:53.040 --> 01:04:55.980 align:middle line:84%
Let me just call it
x for simplicity.

01:04:55.980 --> 01:05:05.280 align:middle line:90%


01:05:05.280 --> 01:05:07.890 align:middle line:84%
So I also have
introduced the notation

01:05:07.890 --> 01:05:13.680 align:middle line:84%
that the pi is
equal to p plus eA.

01:05:13.680 --> 01:05:24.040 align:middle line:90%


01:05:24.040 --> 01:05:26.650 align:middle line:84%
So now you see the difference
between these two equations.

01:05:26.650 --> 01:05:29.540 align:middle line:90%


01:05:29.540 --> 01:05:35.260 align:middle line:84%
So the mass terms here
have opposite sign.

01:05:35.260 --> 01:05:39.990 align:middle line:84%
When I isolate that
piece, and then

01:05:39.990 --> 01:05:43.770 align:middle line:84%
the mass term for this equation
canceled, but in this equation

01:05:43.770 --> 01:05:45.930 align:middle line:84%
they add together,
this minus 2m.

01:05:45.930 --> 01:05:48.660 align:middle line:90%


01:05:48.660 --> 01:05:51.850 align:middle line:90%
We get this minus 2m.

01:05:51.850 --> 01:05:53.320 align:middle line:84%
So now let's look
at the magnitude

01:05:53.320 --> 01:05:55.070 align:middle line:90%
of each term in this equation.

01:05:55.070 --> 01:06:04.350 align:middle line:84%
So this is like mv squared
X. So this is like m times X.

01:06:04.350 --> 01:06:08.700 align:middle line:90%
So this is just something phi.

01:06:08.700 --> 01:06:10.230 align:middle line:84%
We don't know the
relative magnitude

01:06:10.230 --> 01:06:12.520 align:middle line:84%
between X and the phi,
and so this is also

01:06:12.520 --> 01:06:17.760 align:middle line:84%
mv squared X. We said eA0
should be of order mv squared.

01:06:17.760 --> 01:06:20.400 align:middle line:90%


01:06:20.400 --> 01:06:25.020 align:middle line:84%
So these three terms,
they're all related to X,

01:06:25.020 --> 01:06:29.780 align:middle line:84%
and this term dominates
over these two.

01:06:29.780 --> 01:06:32.540 align:middle line:84%
So you can forget
about these two terms

01:06:32.540 --> 01:06:33.800 align:middle line:90%
in the nonrelativistic limit.

01:06:33.800 --> 01:06:39.840 align:middle line:90%


01:06:39.840 --> 01:06:46.560 align:middle line:84%
So from here, if I call this
equation 1 and this equation 2,

01:06:46.560 --> 01:06:53.550 align:middle line:84%
and from 2 we get in the
nonrelativistic limit,

01:06:53.550 --> 01:07:02.190 align:middle line:84%
we just get 2mX plus sigma
pi acting on phi equal to 0.

01:07:02.190 --> 01:07:09.530 align:middle line:90%


01:07:09.530 --> 01:07:17.510 align:middle line:84%
So now we find that X, we can
now solve X in terms of phi--

01:07:17.510 --> 01:07:21.890 align:middle line:90%
1 over 2m sigma dot pi phi.

01:07:21.890 --> 01:07:32.970 align:middle line:90%


01:07:32.970 --> 01:07:37.540 align:middle line:84%
So now we can plug this
back into this equation.

01:07:37.540 --> 01:07:40.800 align:middle line:90%
So this is equation 3.

01:07:40.800 --> 01:07:47.430 align:middle line:84%
If we plug 3 into
1 again, then we

01:07:47.430 --> 01:07:52.410 align:middle line:84%
get Schrodinger
equation for phi.

01:07:52.410 --> 01:07:54.660 align:middle line:84%
So X is no longer
independent field,

01:07:54.660 --> 01:07:58.040 align:middle line:84%
it's just expressed
in terms of phi.

01:07:58.040 --> 01:07:59.665 align:middle line:84%
So now we get the
equation for phi.

01:07:59.665 --> 01:08:17.470 align:middle line:90%


01:08:17.470 --> 01:08:19.270 align:middle line:84%
So now you see
each term, they are

01:08:19.270 --> 01:08:20.990 align:middle line:90%
of the same order of magnitude.

01:08:20.990 --> 01:08:26.160 align:middle line:84%
So this is mv squared
and this is mv.

01:08:26.160 --> 01:08:28.170 align:middle line:90%
Upstairs pi of order mv.

01:08:28.170 --> 01:08:30.689 align:middle line:84%
So this is m squared v
squared divided by m,

01:08:30.689 --> 01:08:34.479 align:middle line:84%
so this again is mv squared
and eA0 is mv squared.

01:08:34.479 --> 01:08:37.229 align:middle line:84%
So now everything
is nonrelativistic

01:08:37.229 --> 01:08:39.803 align:middle line:90%
and of the same order.

01:08:39.803 --> 01:08:41.720 align:middle line:84%
So now let's look at the
meaning of this term.

01:08:41.720 --> 01:08:48.058 align:middle line:90%


01:08:48.058 --> 01:08:49.850 align:middle line:84%
Now let's look at the
meaning of that term.

01:08:49.850 --> 01:09:08.670 align:middle line:90%


01:09:08.670 --> 01:09:10.718 align:middle line:84%
So that term you can
write explicitly.

01:09:10.718 --> 01:09:19.290 align:middle line:90%


01:09:19.290 --> 01:09:23.370 align:middle line:84%
Sigma i pi i, sigma j pi j,
but remember pi i and pi j,

01:09:23.370 --> 01:09:28.710 align:middle line:84%
they are operators, so you need
to keep the ordering there.

01:09:28.710 --> 01:09:32.069 align:middle line:90%


01:09:32.069 --> 01:09:34.380 align:middle line:84%
So we can just write
down, so we just

01:09:34.380 --> 01:09:43.660 align:middle line:84%
have sigma i sigma j just gives
me delta ij plus i epsilon ijk

01:09:43.660 --> 01:09:46.899 align:middle line:90%
sigma k and then pi i pi j.

01:09:46.899 --> 01:09:51.410 align:middle line:90%


01:09:51.410 --> 01:09:58.300 align:middle line:84%
And so the first term
gives me the pi squared,

01:09:58.300 --> 01:10:04.840 align:middle line:84%
and the second term I can just,
using the antisymmetric in ij,

01:10:04.840 --> 01:10:11.720 align:middle line:84%
I can write it as epsilon ijk
sigma k and the pi i and the pi

01:10:11.720 --> 01:10:12.220 align:middle line:90%
j.

01:10:12.220 --> 01:10:15.150 align:middle line:90%


01:10:15.150 --> 01:10:17.430 align:middle line:84%
So I just write the
commutator in terms of them.

01:10:17.430 --> 01:10:20.840 align:middle line:90%


01:10:20.840 --> 01:10:28.750 align:middle line:84%
So now it's easy to
calculate pi i pi j.

01:10:28.750 --> 01:10:41.235 align:middle line:84%
So this is just minus partial
i plus eAi minus partial j --

01:10:41.235 --> 01:10:42.810 align:middle line:90%
minus i partial j --

01:10:42.810 --> 01:10:45.952 align:middle line:90%
plus eAj.

01:10:45.952 --> 01:10:47.410 align:middle line:84%
So if you calculate
the commutator,

01:10:47.410 --> 01:10:49.000 align:middle line:90%
you just get minus e Fij.

01:10:49.000 --> 01:10:56.470 align:middle line:90%


01:10:56.470 --> 01:11:01.330 align:middle line:84%
And now if you plug this Fij
into here, so epsilon ijk

01:11:01.330 --> 01:11:02.980 align:middle line:90%
times Fij, what do you get?

01:11:02.980 --> 01:11:08.050 align:middle line:90%


01:11:08.050 --> 01:11:10.600 align:middle line:84%
Do you remember when
epsilon ijk multiplied

01:11:10.600 --> 01:11:11.920 align:middle line:90%
by Fij, what do you get?

01:11:11.920 --> 01:11:15.020 align:middle line:90%


01:11:15.020 --> 01:11:17.000 align:middle line:90%
You get B.

01:11:17.000 --> 01:11:20.330 align:middle line:84%
So now this equation, when
you plug this in here,

01:11:20.330 --> 01:11:26.770 align:middle line:84%
and then this just
becomes pi squared plus--

01:11:26.770 --> 01:11:27.670 align:middle line:90%
just make sure.

01:11:27.670 --> 01:11:34.490 align:middle line:90%


01:11:34.490 --> 01:11:49.310 align:middle line:84%
e sigma dot B. Because
Fij multiplied by the Fijk

01:11:49.310 --> 01:11:53.944 align:middle line:84%
just gets Bk and Bk sigma
k, just sigma dot B.

01:11:53.944 --> 01:11:57.353 align:middle line:90%
AUDIENCE: [INAUDIBLE]

01:11:57.353 --> 01:11:58.630 align:middle line:90%


01:11:58.630 --> 01:12:02.420 align:middle line:84%
HONG LIU: Yeah, it's one half
epsilon ijk times Fij give you.

01:12:02.420 --> 01:12:06.520 align:middle line:90%


01:12:06.520 --> 01:12:11.370 align:middle line:84%
So if you use one
half epsilon ijk Fij.

01:12:11.370 --> 01:12:18.600 align:middle line:90%


01:12:18.600 --> 01:12:19.890 align:middle line:90%
OK, good.

01:12:19.890 --> 01:12:22.770 align:middle line:90%
We are there.

01:12:22.770 --> 01:12:26.340 align:middle line:90%
So now we are done, essentially.

01:12:26.340 --> 01:12:29.160 align:middle line:84%
So now the Schrodinger
equation, now we

01:12:29.160 --> 01:12:33.360 align:middle line:84%
get the partial t
phi equal to H phi.

01:12:33.360 --> 01:12:37.730 align:middle line:90%
Now H is equal to p squared.

01:12:37.730 --> 01:12:40.940 align:middle line:90%
So now you have pi squared.

01:12:40.940 --> 01:12:43.370 align:middle line:84%
So pi squared, if I
write it explicitly,

01:12:43.370 --> 01:12:49.400 align:middle line:84%
is p plus eA squared
divided by 2m, then

01:12:49.400 --> 01:12:56.360 align:middle line:84%
plus e divided by 2m sigma
dot B, come from this term.

01:12:56.360 --> 01:12:59.520 align:middle line:90%


01:12:59.520 --> 01:13:02.310 align:middle line:90%
And then the last term is eA0.

01:13:02.310 --> 01:13:06.110 align:middle line:90%


01:13:06.110 --> 01:13:12.340 align:middle line:84%
So now if you recognize
this part of the Hamiltonian

01:13:12.340 --> 01:13:17.050 align:middle line:84%
is precisely what you get when
you couple Schrodinger equation

01:13:17.050 --> 01:13:20.170 align:middle line:90%
to your electromagnetic fields.

01:13:20.170 --> 01:13:24.020 align:middle line:84%
You just add the p plus eA
for the vector potential

01:13:24.020 --> 01:13:26.740 align:middle line:90%
and here you get eA0.

01:13:26.740 --> 01:13:28.820 align:middle line:84%
But now here you get
the additional term,

01:13:28.820 --> 01:13:31.980 align:middle line:84%
so this is called
the Pauli term.

01:13:31.980 --> 01:13:34.990 align:middle line:84%
When the particle has
spin, has magnetic moment,

01:13:34.990 --> 01:13:36.460 align:middle line:84%
then you have an
additional term.

01:13:36.460 --> 01:13:38.350 align:middle line:90%
So this term can be interpreted.

01:13:38.350 --> 01:13:42.865 align:middle line:84%
So remember, when a particle
has a magnetic moment.

01:13:42.865 --> 01:13:54.640 align:middle line:90%


01:13:54.640 --> 01:13:59.790 align:middle line:84%
So when a particle
has a magnetic moment,

01:13:59.790 --> 01:14:05.640 align:middle line:84%
then you have a piece
corresponding to mu dot B.

01:14:05.640 --> 01:14:07.980 align:middle line:84%
If you compare this
with that term,

01:14:07.980 --> 01:14:09.930 align:middle line:90%
then we conclude that the mu--

01:14:09.930 --> 01:14:12.360 align:middle line:84%
So in this case,
compare that term.

01:14:12.360 --> 01:14:22.380 align:middle line:84%
That term will be equal
to e 2m sigma dot B.

01:14:22.380 --> 01:14:27.390 align:middle line:84%
So now we conclude, from here
you can read what's the mu.

01:14:27.390 --> 01:14:35.050 align:middle line:84%
mu just minus e divided
by 2m times 2 times sigma

01:14:35.050 --> 01:14:36.730 align:middle line:90%
divided by 2.

01:14:36.730 --> 01:14:41.770 align:middle line:84%
So if you compare with
this, you find that the g

01:14:41.770 --> 01:14:44.916 align:middle line:90%
is exactly equal to 2.

01:14:44.916 --> 01:14:49.010 align:middle line:90%
You find g exactly equal to 2.

01:14:49.010 --> 01:14:52.100 align:middle line:84%
And so this way, you see
actually the Dirac equation

01:14:52.100 --> 01:14:57.140 align:middle line:84%
contains the information the
electron has magnetic moment.

01:14:57.140 --> 01:14:58.940 align:middle line:90%
It has a magnetic moment.

01:14:58.940 --> 01:15:00.020 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

01:15:00.020 --> 01:15:00.468 align:middle line:84%
AUDIENCE: [INAUDIBLE]
would we expect

01:15:00.468 --> 01:15:01.926 align:middle line:84%
g equal to 2 for
all fermions then?

01:15:01.926 --> 01:15:07.860 align:middle line:90%


01:15:07.860 --> 01:15:10.200 align:middle line:90%
HONG LIU: Yeah, yeah, yeah.

01:15:10.200 --> 01:15:13.080 align:middle line:84%
AUDIENCE: Even if we look at
these perturbative calculations

01:15:13.080 --> 01:15:15.247 align:middle line:84%
like the 1 plus 0.001, etc.,
that should apply also?

01:15:15.247 --> 01:15:19.650 align:middle line:90%


01:15:19.650 --> 01:15:21.535 align:middle line:90%
HONG LIU: No, no, no.

01:15:21.535 --> 01:15:23.160 align:middle line:84%
Because the correction
can be different

01:15:23.160 --> 01:15:26.060 align:middle line:84%
for different formulas
because different formulas,

01:15:26.060 --> 01:15:28.080 align:middle line:84%
they have different
interactions.

01:15:28.080 --> 01:15:31.440 align:middle line:84%
And so that will change
this vertex differently.

01:15:31.440 --> 01:15:34.310 align:middle line:84%
For example, muons and
electrons will be different.

01:15:34.310 --> 01:15:38.030 align:middle line:90%


01:15:38.030 --> 01:15:38.540 align:middle line:90%
Yes.

01:15:38.540 --> 01:15:39.606 align:middle line:90%
AUDIENCE: [INAUDIBLE].

01:15:39.606 --> 01:15:49.700 align:middle line:90%


01:15:49.700 --> 01:15:52.640 align:middle line:84%
HONG LIU: Well, in the high
speed you can no longer--

01:15:52.640 --> 01:15:58.290 align:middle line:84%
So when you have high speeds or
this effect, they mix together.

01:15:58.290 --> 01:16:01.180 align:middle line:84%
So relativistically,
you can no longer

01:16:01.180 --> 01:16:03.610 align:middle line:84%
isolate the contribution
from the angular momentum

01:16:03.610 --> 01:16:05.153 align:middle line:84%
from your orbital
angular momentum,

01:16:05.153 --> 01:16:06.070 align:middle line:90%
spin angular momentum.

01:16:06.070 --> 01:16:07.320 align:middle line:90%
They all come together.

01:16:07.320 --> 01:16:09.070 align:middle line:84%
So it's only in the
long relativistic case

01:16:09.070 --> 01:16:11.410 align:middle line:90%
you can isolate like this.

01:16:11.410 --> 01:16:13.605 align:middle line:84%
So normally when we talk
about magnetic moments,

01:16:13.605 --> 01:16:14.980 align:middle line:84%
we always think
it about in terms

01:16:14.980 --> 01:16:16.510 align:middle line:90%
of nonrelativistic situation.

01:16:16.510 --> 01:16:20.350 align:middle line:90%


01:16:20.350 --> 01:16:24.610 align:middle line:90%
So now just some final words.

01:16:24.610 --> 01:16:27.320 align:middle line:90%
Just erased that number.

01:16:27.320 --> 01:16:31.250 align:middle line:84%
So Schwinger then
did this calculation.

01:16:31.250 --> 01:16:38.410 align:middle line:84%
So including this diagram,
Schwinger did this calculation,

01:16:38.410 --> 01:16:42.850 align:middle line:84%
and then he found that
there's a small correction.

01:16:42.850 --> 01:16:45.370 align:middle line:84%
So normally, its called
-- say if I call it --

01:16:45.370 --> 01:16:51.890 align:middle line:84%
1 plus F. And so this
is the correction.

01:16:51.890 --> 01:16:56.570 align:middle line:84%
And then the correction, which
Schwinger first calculated,

01:16:56.570 --> 01:17:00.800 align:middle line:84%
is given by alpha
just divided by 2pi.

01:17:00.800 --> 01:17:03.740 align:middle line:84%
The reason it's alpha is
because here there's a e here,

01:17:03.740 --> 01:17:07.700 align:middle line:84%
here there's an e, so
e squared is alpha.

01:17:07.700 --> 01:17:09.980 align:middle line:84%
So all this
complicated calculation

01:17:09.980 --> 01:17:13.703 align:middle line:84%
you do, essentially you
find this 1 over 2pi.

01:17:13.703 --> 01:17:15.620 align:middle line:84%
Because this correction
has to be proportional

01:17:15.620 --> 01:17:20.450 align:middle line:84%
to alpha, and this number you
do a very hard calculation,

01:17:20.450 --> 01:17:22.850 align:middle line:90%
you find it's 1 over 2pi.

01:17:22.850 --> 01:17:26.270 align:middle line:84%
And then this actually agreed
with experiment very well.

01:17:26.270 --> 01:17:31.310 align:middle line:84%
So this is first calculated
by Schwinger in 1948.

01:17:31.310 --> 01:17:36.200 align:middle line:84%
So this was really a
theoretical triumph at that time

01:17:36.200 --> 01:17:40.910 align:middle line:84%
and agreed very well
with experiments.

01:17:40.910 --> 01:17:45.710 align:middle line:84%
So then people then
calculate to higher orders.

01:17:45.710 --> 01:17:50.950 align:middle line:84%
So the next order must be
proportional to alpha squared,

01:17:50.950 --> 01:17:54.932 align:middle line:84%
so we can parameterize by
alpha divided by 2pi squared,

01:17:54.932 --> 01:17:56.140 align:middle line:90%
and then with some number a2.

01:17:56.140 --> 01:17:59.340 align:middle line:90%


01:17:59.340 --> 01:18:01.840 align:middle line:84%
You do an even more complicated
calculation, much, much more

01:18:01.840 --> 01:18:04.420 align:middle line:84%
complicated calculation, you
find that this a2, again, it's

01:18:04.420 --> 01:18:05.910 align:middle line:90%
a single number.

01:18:05.910 --> 01:18:08.700 align:middle line:84%
And this contains
seven diagrams.

01:18:08.700 --> 01:18:12.210 align:middle line:84%
So this is one diagram, but
when you go to the next order,

01:18:12.210 --> 01:18:14.810 align:middle line:84%
actually involving
seven diagrams.

01:18:14.810 --> 01:18:18.290 align:middle line:90%
And that was calculated in 1957.

01:18:18.290 --> 01:18:23.780 align:middle line:84%
Again, it was a very important
thing to do at that time,

01:18:23.780 --> 01:18:26.420 align:middle line:84%
because just to
check whether QED,

01:18:26.420 --> 01:18:30.530 align:middle line:84%
because the experimental
accuracy was at the level

01:18:30.530 --> 01:18:32.315 align:middle line:84%
actually you can
compare this number.

01:18:32.315 --> 01:18:37.160 align:middle line:90%


01:18:37.160 --> 01:18:39.920 align:middle line:84%
Actually, also there's
some kind of story

01:18:39.920 --> 01:18:42.830 align:middle line:84%
behind this number,
which at the beginning

01:18:42.830 --> 01:18:45.500 align:middle line:84%
they calculated
wrong, et cetera.

01:18:45.500 --> 01:18:48.224 align:middle line:84%
So now you can also
calculate the next one, a3.

01:18:48.224 --> 01:18:50.990 align:middle line:90%


01:18:50.990 --> 01:18:53.720 align:middle line:84%
You can parameterize
again by cube.

01:18:53.720 --> 01:18:57.395 align:middle line:84%
And now this now
includes 72 diagrams.

01:18:57.395 --> 01:19:00.780 align:middle line:90%


01:19:00.780 --> 01:19:03.700 align:middle line:90%
And it took two physicists--

01:19:03.700 --> 01:19:05.730 align:middle line:90%
I won't write down their names--

01:19:05.730 --> 01:19:09.370 align:middle line:84%
it took them 25 years
to calculate it.

01:19:09.370 --> 01:19:10.530 align:middle line:90%
So actually they used it.

01:19:10.530 --> 01:19:14.320 align:middle line:90%


01:19:14.320 --> 01:19:18.600 align:middle line:84%
So in 1996 they finally
calculated this.

01:19:18.600 --> 01:19:26.090 align:middle line:84%
But now if you want to say,
oh, let's try to calculate a4,

01:19:26.090 --> 01:19:29.290 align:middle line:84%
this includes 891
diagrams just in QED.

01:19:29.290 --> 01:19:32.350 align:middle line:90%


01:19:32.350 --> 01:19:35.180 align:middle line:84%
And actually, this is also
calculated using computer.

01:19:35.180 --> 01:19:39.170 align:middle line:90%


01:19:39.170 --> 01:19:40.920 align:middle line:84%
And also, you can
calculate this for muon.

01:19:40.920 --> 01:19:45.540 align:middle line:90%


01:19:45.540 --> 01:19:47.220 align:middle line:84%
At a certain level,
you also need

01:19:47.220 --> 01:19:49.810 align:middle line:84%
to include the contribution
from other interactions,

01:19:49.810 --> 01:19:53.800 align:middle line:84%
not just QED, weak
interactions, et cetera.

01:19:53.800 --> 01:19:59.160 align:middle line:84%
Anyway, so the reason you want
to calculate such a number

01:19:59.160 --> 01:20:03.420 align:middle line:84%
to very high accuracy
is because this F

01:20:03.420 --> 01:20:08.585 align:middle line:84%
can be measured to very, very
high accuracy experimentally.

01:20:08.585 --> 01:20:09.960 align:middle line:84%
So actually,
experimentally, this

01:20:09.960 --> 01:20:15.010 align:middle line:84%
is one of the most accurately
measured number in physics.

01:20:15.010 --> 01:20:18.755 align:middle line:84%
They can measure this F
to order of 10 to the -12.

01:20:18.755 --> 01:20:29.790 align:middle line:90%


01:20:29.790 --> 01:20:32.550 align:middle line:84%
I think at the
theoretical level,

01:20:32.550 --> 01:20:34.950 align:middle line:84%
you actually cannot calculate
to this level accuracy,

01:20:34.950 --> 01:20:42.790 align:middle line:84%
but still you can compare to
very, very good agreement.

01:20:42.790 --> 01:20:48.975 align:middle line:84%
So QED actually describes
nature very, very well.

01:20:48.975 --> 01:20:52.020 align:middle line:90%


01:20:52.020 --> 01:20:55.785 align:middle line:90%
So I think that's all.

01:20:55.785 --> 01:21:01.170 align:middle line:90%


01:21:01.170 --> 01:21:04.020 align:middle line:84%
I'm honored and very happy
to have this opportunity

01:21:04.020 --> 01:21:09.270 align:middle line:84%
to take you to this first part
of the journey to quantum field

01:21:09.270 --> 01:21:14.580 align:middle line:84%
theory, and I want
